#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:4
msgid "iommu-testdev — IOMMU test device for bare-metal testing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:7
msgid "Overview"
msgstr "概覽"

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:8
msgid ""
"``iommu-testdev`` is a minimal, test-only PCI device designed to exercise "
"IOMMU translation (such as ARM SMMUv3) without requiring firmware or a guest "
"OS. Tests can populate IOMMU translation tables with known values and "
"trigger DMA operations that flow through the IOMMU translation path. It is "
"**not** a faithful PCIe endpoint and must be considered a QEMU-internal test "
"vehicle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:15
msgid "Key Features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:16
msgid "**Bare-metal IOMMU testing**: No guest kernel or firmware required"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:17
msgid ""
"**Configurable DMA attributes**: Supports address space configuration via "
"MMIO registers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:19
msgid ""
"**Deterministic verification**: Write-then-read DMA pattern with automatic "
"result checking"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:23
msgid "Status"
msgstr ""

