msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:29
msgid "Device Interface"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:30
msgid "The device exposes a single PCI BAR0 with 32-bit MMIO registers:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:32
msgid ""
"``ITD_REG_DMA_TRIGGERING`` (0x00): Read triggers DMA and consumes the armed "
"request"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:34
msgid "``ITD_REG_DMA_GVA_LO`` (0x04): DMA IOVA bits [31:0]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:35
msgid "``ITD_REG_DMA_GVA_HI`` (0x08): DMA IOVA bits [63:32]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:36
msgid ""
"``ITD_REG_DMA_GPA_LO`` (0x1C): DMA GPA bits [31:0] for readback validation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:37
msgid ""
"``ITD_REG_DMA_GPA_HI`` (0x20): DMA GPA bits [63:32] for readback validation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:38
msgid "``ITD_REG_DMA_LEN`` (0x0C): DMA transfer length"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:39
msgid ""
"``ITD_REG_DMA_RESULT`` (0x10): DMA result (0=success, 0xffffffff=idle, "
"0xfffffffe=armed)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:41
msgid ""
"``ITD_REG_DMA_DBELL`` (0x14): Write 1 to arm DMA, write 0 to disarm. Arming "
"only marks the request and sets BUSY (no latch/check), but it provides an "
"explicit gate for qtests and leaves room for async/latching."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:44
msgid ""
"``ITD_REG_DMA_ATTRS`` (0x18): DMA attributes which shadow some fields in "
"MemTxAttrs:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:47
msgid "bit[0]: secure (1=Secure, 0=Non-Secure)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:48
msgid "bits[2:1]: ArmSecuritySpace (0=Secure, 1=Non-Secure)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:49
msgid ""
"bit[3]: space_valid (1=space is valid, 0=ignore space and default to Non-"
"Secure) ``space`` field in MemTxAttrs is consumed only when ``space_valid`` "
"is set. For Secure/Non-Secure, ``secure`` and ``space`` must match; "
"mismatches return ``ITD_DMA_ERR_BAD_ATTRS``. Other bits are reserved but can "
"be wired up easily if future tests need to pass extra attributes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:56
msgid "Translation Setup Workflow"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:57
msgid ""
"``iommu-testdev`` never builds SMMU/AMD-Vi/RISC-V IOMMU structures on its "
"own. Architecture-specific construction lives entirely in qtest/libqos "
"helpers. Those helpers populate guest memory with page tables/architecture-"
"specific structures and program the emulated IOMMU registers directly. See "
"the ``qsmmu_setup_and_enable_translation()`` function in ``tests/qtest/"
"libqos/qos-smmuv3.c`` for an example of how SMMUv3 translation is set up for "
"this device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:66
msgid "DMA Operation Flow"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:67
msgid "Arming semantics:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:69
msgid ""
"Writing ``DMA_DBELL`` with bit0=1 marks the request armed and sets "
"``DMA_RESULT`` to BUSY. It does not latch GVA/LEN/ATTRS; values are sampled "
"when ``DMA_TRIGGERING`` is read."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:72
msgid ""
"Writing ``DMA_DBELL`` with bit0=0 disarms the request and sets "
"``DMA_RESULT`` to IDLE."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:74
msgid ""
"Reading ``DMA_TRIGGERING`` consumes the armed request and clears the armed "
"state, even on error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:77
msgid ""
"The flow would be split into these steps, mainly for timing control and "
"debuggability: qtests can easily exercise and assert distinct paths "
"(NOT_ARMED, BAD_LEN, TX/RD failures, mismatch) instead of having all side "
"effects hidden behind a single step: 1. Test programs IOMMU translation "
"tables 2. Test configures DMA IOVA (GVA_LO/HI), GPA for readback, length, "
"and attributes 3. Test writes 1 to DMA_DBELL to arm the operation 4. Test "
"reads DMA_TRIGGERING to execute DMA 5. Test polls DMA_RESULT:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:87
msgid "0x00000000: Success"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:88
msgid ""
"0xFFFFFFFE: Armed (waiting for trigger). DMA runs synchronously, so BUSY is "
"not observed once the trigger read completes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:90
msgid "0xDEAD0006: Bad attrs (secure/space mismatch for S/NS)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:91
msgid "0xDEAD000X: Various error codes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:93
msgid ""
"The device performs a write-then-read sequence using a known pattern "
"(0x12345678) and verifies data integrity automatically."
msgstr ""

