msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:121
msgid ""
"When the IOMMU sits on the same PCI root complex (``pci.0``), the device is "
"placed behind it automatically. For other PCI topologies, specify the bus "
"explicitly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:126
msgid "Limitations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:127
msgid "No realistic PCIe enumeration, MSI/MSI-X, or interrupt handling"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:128
msgid "No ATS/PRI support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:129
msgid "No actual device functionality beyond DMA test pattern"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:130
msgid "Test-only; not suitable for production or machine realism"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:131
msgid ""
"Address space support (Secure/Root/Realm) is architecture-dependent and "
"gated by ``space_valid``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../specs/iommu-testdev.rst:133
msgid ""
"Readback uses the programmed GPA and reads via system memory, avoiding a "
"second IOMMU access for the readback step"
msgstr ""

